CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1962, pg. 10 reads: " "Boning Up" For School - These diligent youngsters need not worry about distractions when they attend the study halls conducted at the Brushton Methodist Church Community Center, one of the many organizations and agencies helping to make team teaching a success in Homewood area. Here two kiddies have their questions answered by volunteer supervisors, Miss Mae Hammann and Gregory Morris. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group of young boys and girls seated at student desks, with volunteers Mae Hammann and Gregory Morris, gathered in classroom for study session in Brushton Methodist Church Community Center, another version
